                <head>283. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>, accompanied by Prime
                    Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName>, left the Mid-Ocean
                    Club at 10:10 a.m. on March 24 and drove to Kindley Air Force Base. The
                    President left Bermuda shortly after 10:30. (Eisenhower Library, President’s
                    Appointment Book) Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName>
                    remained in Bermuda another 3 days. On March 25 and 26, he had conversations
                    with Canadian Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_SLLS1">Louis St.
                        Laurent</persName> and Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_PLB1">Lester
                        B. Pearson</persName>. (<persName corresp="#p_MH1">Harold
                        Macmillan</persName>, <hi rend="italic">Riding the Storm,</hi> page 258)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
